<title>UK: Reed-Elsevier crosses one hurdle for MDL.</title>
<headline>Reed-Elsevier crosses one hurdle for MDL.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The $320 million bid by Anglo-Dutch publishing group Reed-Elsevier for MDL Information Systems crossed one of its obstacles with the pre-merger waiting period expiring on April 10, without the U.S. Federal Trade Commission or Department of Justice seeking additional information.</p>
<p>The tender offer of $32 per share, which Reed-Elsevier made for MDL on March 24, is scheduled to expire on April 24.</p>
